            Despite the fact that the principle has been in the treaty all these years, there has been a steady accretion of power by the European Union and its institutions. Even if we manage to do things better in future, there remain in the acquis communautaire many breaches of the principle. There is no appetite in the Convention for revisiting the past and putting right the breaches.</p><p>
            To give a direct answer to my hon. Friend, very few other member states have the same tradition of parliamentary democracy and instinct for self-
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_340wh' title='Col. 340WH &mdash; HC Deb 30 January 2003 vol 398 c340WH' name='column_340wh' href='#column_340wh' rel='bookmark'>340WH</a>
